page.text: The purpose of this safety study is to investigate the existing safety performance and to determine
appropriate potential countermeasures to alleviate congestion and reduce collisions along US-20A for
Main Street to just before Hallett Avenue (Fulton-Lucas Road).
the North side of the corridor there
is a large number of businesses drives that are closely spaced which creates problems with traffic flow
due to vehicles crossing multiple lanes of traffic.
Currently the existing roadway of US-20A consists of two (2) eastbound through lanes, two (2)
westbound through lanes and a center two-way left turn lane, a total of five (5) lanes. At the
intersection of US-20A and SR-64 (Main St), a signalized cross intersection, the two-way left turn lane
transitions to a left turn lane for east and westbound US-20A to turn left onto Main St. The north and
south legs of Main St consist of a single through/left/right lane and a receiving lane. The signals at the
intersection are on overhead span wire with supports in all four corners of the intersection.
Crash reports were obtained between January 1st of 2010 and December 31st of 2012. The reports
were checked for accuracy by cross-checking them with actual police reports. During this three-year
period a total of 37 crashes occurred in the section. Of these 19 crashes, ten (10) occurred at the
intersection of US-20A and SR-64 (Main St.). Of the 19 crashes, seven (7) were contributed to failure to
yield, four (4) were contributed to running the red light, two (2) were contributed to an improper lane
change, two (2) were contributed to an improper turn, two (2) were contributed to following to close,
one (1) were contributed to driving left of center, one (1) was contributed to improper backing. There
were eight (8) injury crashes in the intersection.
The probable causes or deficiencies is the corridor were identified through detailed analysis of the crash patterns,
roadway conditions, traffic volumes, traffic speed, and the existing traffic control devices.
Through this analysis possible safety items were identified within the corridor as follows:
1. Angle and left turn crashes along the north side of the corridor related to business traffic, access
2. Left turn and angle crashes at the intersection of US-20A and Main St.
3. Signal head visibility within the section.
